  "body": "I am currently using a forked network from getblock.io bsc archive node.\r\nI realized that\r\n\r\nFirst terminal\r\n1. Run node in\r\n\r\nSecond terminal\r\n1. Deploy contract and save the address (eg, **0x1234**)\r\n2. Run test and retrieve contract at **0x1234** <-- contract doesn't seem to exist?\r\n\r\nReproducible repo - https://github.com/ShaunLWM/hardhat-test\r\n1. yarn network\r\n2. yarn deploy\r\n3. yarn test\r\n\r\n\r\nThe test in `sample-test.ts` will have an error `Error: call revert exception (method=\"greet()\", errorArgs=null, errorName=null, errorSignature=null, reason=null, code=CALL_EXCEPTION, version=abi/5.4.0)`\r\n\r\nFor some reason, deployment deloys Token to `0x36C02dA8a0983159322a80FFE9F24b1acfF8B570` and Greeter to `0x809d550fca64d94Bd9F66E60752A544199cfAC3D`. However, if I were to deploy Greeter again in my test, it overrides to `0x36C02dA8a0983159322a80FFE9F24b1acfF8B570`. Are these address hardcoded or tied to getblock archive blockchain?",
